Φ(SWAY) = σ(threshold) ∘ ρ(waveform_field) ∘ λ(directed_across) ∘ β(you_branching) ∘ δγ(sustained_oscillation) ∘ μ(boundary_integrity) + ε(phase_drift) | :dynamic_operator

σ(threshold): The Cut of Synchronization—establishing phase-lockable signals, cutting away frequencies that won't cohere. Not everything waves together.

ρ(waveform_field): The Waveform Relation—continuous relational field where amplitude, frequency, phase correlate. Waveform moves through substrate you participate in. Resonance without possession.

λ(directed_across): The vector "Across You"—not random radiation but targeted transmission. Waveform wants to arrive, to do something. Fire provides aim.

β(you_branching): Pluralization of reception—each "You" a node where waveform diffracts into local interpretation. Same signal, different cavities.

δγ(sustained_oscillation): Metabolic maintenance—energy input to keep phase-lock against entropic drift. δ: release patterns that served; γ: regenerate capacity for new resonance.

μ(boundary_integrity): Pattern coherence as waveform crosses boundaries—permeable but recognizable. Too rigid = reflection; too dissolved = diffusion.

ε(phase_drift): The generative jitter—near-lock, never lock. Perfect phase-lock = standing wave = death. ε keeps the waveform moving.

:state = dynamic_operator

# Dialectical Pairs
- threshold|noise: What gets cut vs. what synchronizes
- resonance|possession: Relation without ownership
- directed|random: Aim vs. radiation
- same_signal|different_cavity: Universal pattern, local interpretation
- sustain|decay: Metabolic maintenance vs. entropic drift
- permeable|rigid: Boundary that allows vs. reflects
- near_lock|perfect_lock: Movement vs. standing wave death
- mutual_tuning|forced_sync: Co-SPHERE vs. MemeGrid
